  "root_text": {
    "snp2.4:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 2.4 ",
    "snp2.4:0.2": "Maṅgalasutta ",
    "snp2.4:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "snp2.4:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "snp2.4:1.3": "Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṁ jetavanaṁ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. ",
    "snp2.4:1.4": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavantaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "snp2.4:2.1": "“Bahū devā manussā ca, ",
    "snp2.4:2.2": "maṅgalāni acintayuṁ; ",
    "snp2.4:2.3": "Ākaṅkhamānā sotthānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.4:2.4": "brūhi maṅgalamuttamaṁ”. ",
    "snp2.4:3.1": "“Asevanā ca bālānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.4:3.2": "paṇḍitānañca sevanā; ",
    "snp2.4:3.3": "Pūjā ca pūjaneyyānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.4:3.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:4.1": "Patirūpadesavāso ca, ",
    "snp2.4:4.2": "pubbe ca katapuññatā; ",
    "snp2.4:4.3": "Attasammāpaṇidhi ca, ",
    "snp2.4:4.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:5.1": "Bāhusaccañca sippañca, ",
    "snp2.4:5.2": "vinayo ca susikkhito; ",
    "snp2.4:5.3": "Subhāsitā ca yā vācā, ",
    "snp2.4:5.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:6.1": "Mātāpitu upaṭṭhānaṁ, ",
    "snp2.4:6.2": "puttadārassa saṅgaho; ",
    "snp2.4:6.3": "Anākulā ca kammantā, ",
    "snp2.4:6.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:7.1": "Dānañca dhammacariyā ca, ",
    "snp2.4:7.2": "ñātakānañca saṅgaho; ",
    "snp2.4:7.3": "Anavajjāni kammāni, ",
    "snp2.4:7.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:8.1": "Āratī viratī pāpā, ",
    "snp2.4:8.2": "majjapānā ca saṁyamo; ",
    "snp2.4:8.3": "Appamādo ca dhammesu, ",
    "snp2.4:8.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:9.1": "Gāravo ca nivāto ca, ",
    "snp2.4:9.2": "santuṭṭhi ca kataññutā; ",
    "snp2.4:9.3": "Kālena dhammassavanaṁ, ",
    "snp2.4:9.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:10.1": "Khantī ca sovacassatā, ",
    "snp2.4:10.2": "samaṇānañca dassanaṁ; ",
    "snp2.4:10.3": "Kālena dhammasākacchā, ",
    "snp2.4:10.4": "etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:11.1": "Tapo ca brahmacariyañca, ",
    "snp2.4:11.2": "Ariyasaccāna dassanaṁ; ",
    "snp2.4:11.3": "Nibbānasacchikiriyā ca, ",
    "snp2.4:11.4": "Etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:12.1": "Phuṭṭhassa lokadhammehi, ",
    "snp2.4:12.2": "Cittaṁ yassa na kampati; ",
    "snp2.4:12.3": "Asokaṁ virajaṁ khemaṁ, ",
    "snp2.4:12.4": "Etaṁ maṅgalamuttamaṁ. ",
    "snp2.4:13.1": "Etādisāni katvāna, ",
    "snp2.4:13.2": "Sabbattha maparājitā; ",
    "snp2.4:13.3": "Sabbattha sotthiṁ gacchanti, ",
    "snp2.4:13.4": "Taṁ tesaṁ maṅgalamuttaman”ti. ",
    "snp2.4:13.5": "Maṅgalasuttaṁ catutthaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp2.4:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 2.4 ",
    "snp2.4:0.2": "Blessings ",
    "snp2.4:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "snp2.4:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ",
    "snp2.4:1.3": "Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. ",
    "snp2.4:1.4": "Standing to one side, that deity addressed the Buddha in verse: ",
    "snp2.4:2.1": "“Many gods and humans ",
    "snp2.4:2.2": "have thought about blessings ",
    "snp2.4:2.3": "desiring well-being: ",
    "snp2.4:2.4": "declare the highest blessing.” ",
    "snp2.4:3.1": "“Not to fraternize with fools, ",
    "snp2.4:3.2": "but to fraternize with the wise, ",
    "snp2.4:3.3": "and honoring those worthy of honor: ",
    "snp2.4:3.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:4.1": "Living in a suitable region, ",
    "snp2.4:4.2": "having made merit in the past, ",
    "snp2.4:4.3": "being rightly resolved in oneself, ",
    "snp2.4:4.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:5.1": "Education and a craft, ",
    "snp2.4:5.2": "discipline and training, ",
    "snp2.4:5.3": "and well-spoken speech: ",
    "snp2.4:5.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:6.1": "Caring for mother and father, ",
    "snp2.4:6.2": "kindness to children and partners, ",
    "snp2.4:6.3": "and unstressful work: ",
    "snp2.4:6.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:7.1": "Giving and righteous conduct, ",
    "snp2.4:7.2": "kindness to relatives, ",
    "snp2.4:7.3": "blameless deeds: ",
    "snp2.4:7.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:8.1": "Desisting and abstaining from evil, ",
    "snp2.4:8.2": "avoiding drinking liquor, ",
    "snp2.4:8.3": "diligence in good qualities: ",
    "snp2.4:8.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:9.1": "Respect and placidity, ",
    "snp2.4:9.2": "contentment and gratitude, ",
    "snp2.4:9.3": "and timely listening to the teaching: ",
    "snp2.4:9.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:10.1": "Patience, being easy to admonish, ",
    "snp2.4:10.2": "the sight of ascetics, ",
    "snp2.4:10.3": "and timely discussion of the teaching: ",
    "snp2.4:10.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:11.1": "Fervor and chastity ",
    "snp2.4:11.2": "seeing the noble truths, ",
    "snp2.4:11.3": "and realization of extinguishment: ",
    "snp2.4:11.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:12.1": "Though touched by worldly things, ",
    "snp2.4:12.2": "their mind does not tremble; ",
    "snp2.4:12.3": "sorrowless, stainless, secure, ",
    "snp2.4:12.4": "this is the highest blessing. ",
    "snp2.4:13.1": "Having completed these things, ",
    "snp2.4:13.2": "undefeated everywhere; ",
    "snp2.4:13.3": "everywhere they go in safety: ",
    "snp2.4:13.4": "this is their highest blessing.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp2.4:3.3": "pūjaneyyānaṁ → pūjanīyānaṁ (bj, sya-all, km, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp2.4:4.3": "Attasammāpaṇidhi → attasammāpaṇīdhī (katthaci) ",
    "snp2.4:9.3": "dhammassavanaṁ → dhammasavaṇaṁ (bj); dhammasavanaṁ (si, pts-vp-pli1, mr) "
  },
